        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(synology-chat): remove local deliver timeout",
        "body": "Fixes #59966.\n\n## What changed\n\nRemoved the Synology Chat webhook handler's local `Promise.race` wrapper with the hardcoded 120s timeout. The handler now awaits `params.deliver(...)` directly, so the channel layer no longer overrides the core agent timeout configuration.\n\nAdded focused regression coverage proving a successful webhook delivery path no longer schedules a 120000ms timeout.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed:** Synology Chat webhook delivery should not install a local 120s timeout wrapper around `deliver`; timeout policy should remain with the core agent runtime instead of being overridden by the channel handler.\n\n**Real environment tested:** macOS arm64, Node v26.0.0, pnpm, OpenClaw checkout at `/Users/allahyar/Documents/fastino-tasks/openclaw-tui-59966`.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:** I exercised the Synology Chat webhook handler path from this branch with a direct `createWebhookHandler` probe that records the `setTimeout` delays scheduled during one authorized webhook request, then ran the focused Synology Chat webhook test shard:\n\n```text\n$ pnpm exec tsx --conditions=browser -e \"<direct createWebhookHandler probe that records setTimeout delays during one authorized Synology webhook request>\"\n$ pnpm test extensions/synology-chat/src/webhook-handler.test.ts --reporter=verbose\n$ pnpm exec oxfmt --check extensions/synology-chat/src/webhook-handler.ts extensions/synology-chat/src/webhook-handler.test.ts\n$ pnpm exec oxlint extensions/synology-chat/src/webhook-handler.ts extensions/synology-chat/src/webhook-handler.test.ts --report-unused-disable-directives-severity error\n$ git diff --check\n```\n\n**Before evidence optional:** The same direct handler probe on a clean `origin/main` checkout produced this terminal output:\n\n```text\n{\n  \"status\": 204,\n  \"delays\": [\n    120000\n  ],\n  \"hasHardcoded120sTimeout\": true\n}\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix:** The same direct handler probe on this branch produced this copied terminal output:\n\n```text\n{\n  \"status\": 204,\n  \"delays\": [],\n  \"hasHardcoded120sTimeout\": false\n}\n```\n\nThe focused regression test also passed on this branch:\n\n```text\n$ pnpm test extensions/synology-chat/src/webhook-handler.test.ts --reporter=verbose\n✓ |extension-messaging| extensions/synology-chat/src/webhook-handler.test.ts > createWebhookHandler > awaits deliver directly with no local hardcoded timeout wrapper 1ms\n\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  23 passed (23)\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard in 7.02s\n```\n\nFormat, lint, and whitespace checks passed:\n\n```text\n$ pnpm exec oxfmt --check extensions/synology-chat/src/webhook-handler.ts extensions/synology-chat/src/webhook-handler.test.ts\nAll matched files use the correct format.\n\n$ pnpm exec oxlint extensions/synology-chat/src/webhook-handler.ts extensions/synology-chat/src/webhook-handler.test.ts --report-unused-disable-directives-severity error\n# passed with no output\n\n$ git diff --check\n# passed with no output\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** The authorized Synology Chat webhook path still returns HTTP 204 and calls through delivery, but the copied terminal output from the handler probe shows no local `120000`ms timeout is scheduled after this patch.\n\n**Not tested:** Live Synology Chat network delivery against a real NAS instance.\n",
